WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.120
I think food has always been a very big part of my family

00:00:04.120 --> 00:00:06.240
with my grandfather working in the food industry,

00:00:06.240 --> 00:00:08.960
although I never saw my grandfather cook.

00:00:08.960 --> 00:00:11.960
My grandmother did all the cooking at home

00:00:11.960 --> 00:00:14.080
and he was definitely more in the management side.

00:00:14.080 --> 00:00:17.840
And I think that's where the employment ideals came from.

00:00:17.840 --> 00:00:20.560
But my mom, her love language is cooking.

00:00:20.560 --> 00:00:23.140
And so she taught me to cook.

00:00:23.140 --> 00:00:26.440
And we talk about this with our apprentices as well.

00:00:26.440 --> 00:00:29.760
Cooking is actually a financial skill

00:00:29.760 --> 00:00:31.540
because if you don't know how to cook for yourself,

00:00:31.540 --> 00:00:34.640
eating out is very expensive, it's not as healthy.

00:00:34.640 --> 00:00:36.720
And so that was just kind of ingrained into me

00:00:36.720 --> 00:00:39.400
that we cook to be together, we cook for our health,

00:00:39.400 --> 00:00:42.360
we cook because that's part of life.

00:00:42.360 --> 00:00:45.760
So I think it just, I think it brought my family

00:00:45.760 --> 00:00:50.040
closer to what I was doing, but it just was a good fit.

00:00:50.040 --> 00:00:53.120
I think I was always very into cooking

00:00:53.120 --> 00:00:56.080
and being in the kitchen and nourishing my family.

00:00:56.080 --> 00:00:59.440
I had one child when I started this job, I now have three.

00:00:59.760 --> 00:01:02.360
So yeah, food is a big part of our life.
